<br>
But any mushrooms will do -- white button, crimini (the darker brown ones), or even diced portobellos (mmm!).  Just don't use the canned ones, which by all accounts are totally gross.<br>
<br>
One other vegetable tip -- don't overcook your veggies.  Remember they're going to cook a little bit in the omelet, also.  Mushrooms, onions, and garlic can be sauteed, but you can (should) cook other kinds of veggies like broccoli and squash in the microwave (throw them in a bowl or whatever with about a tablespoon of water, cover with plastic wrap, nuke for about a minute).  <br>
<br>
Broccoli and other green veggies should be emerald green, not olive-colored.  Summer squash should be brilliant yellow.  This method might produce slightly crunchier veggies than you're used to, but they'll be way less bitter and have a lot more flavor (in addition to being neat-looking!).<br>
